cs.NI, cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.DC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper is about Software-Defined Networking (SDN) and its control over the global behavior of the network. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is also likely as the paper discusses formal methods and model checking techniques for verifying properties of SDN networks. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper uses actor-based modelling to represent SDN programs. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is relevant as the paper discusses the verification of concurrent and distributed software. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also relevant as SDN is a distributed networking paradigm.
